# Tanzeem-e-Khawjgan Website - Environment Configuration

# ==============================================================================
# IMPORTANT: This project uses LOCAL CONFIGURATION files, NOT environment variables
# ==============================================================================
# Per constitutional requirements, this project does NOT use .env files.
# All configuration is stored in config/site-config.json
#
# This .env.example file exists only to:
# 1. Document the constitutional requirement
# 2. Prevent accidental .env file creation
# 3. Provide guidance for configuration
#
# ==============================================================================

# DO NOT CREATE .env FILES
# All configuration should be in: config/site-config.json

# ==============================================================================
# CONFIGURATION GUIDE
# ==============================================================================

# To configure the application:
# 1. Open: config/site-config.json
# 2. Update the following fields:

# EMAIL CONFIGURATION (Required for forms to work)
# - Get your API key from: https://resend.com
# - Update: config/site-config.json -> email.resendApiKey
# - Update: config/site-config.json -> email.fromEmail
# - Update: config/site-config.json -> email.adminEmail

# CONTACT INFORMATION (Required for contact page)
# - Update: config/site-config.json -> contact.email
# - Update: config/site-config.json -> contact.phone
# - Update: config/site-config.json -> contact.address
# - Update: config/site-config.json -> contact.coordinates

# SOCIAL MEDIA (Optional)
# - Update: config/site-config.json -> social.facebook
# - Update: config/site-config.json -> social.twitter
# - Update: config/site-config.json -> social.instagram

# ==============================================================================
# QUICK START
# ==============================================================================

# 1. Install dependencies:
#    npm install

# 2. Configure application:
#    Edit config/site-config.json with your details

# 3. Update content:
#    Edit files in config/content/en/

# 4. Run development server:
#    npm run dev

# 5. Build for production:
#    npm run build

# ==============================================================================
# DEPLOYMENT NOTES
# ==============================================================================

# For production deployment:
# - Ensure config/site-config.json has real values (not placeholders)
# - Never commit sensitive API keys to git
# - Use your hosting platform's secrets management for production
# - Or use a separate config/site-config.production.json (gitignored)

# ==============================================================================
